    Description:
  Creates a boilerplate file for a new Stimulus Controller. Pass it a name,
  either CamelCase or snake_case. Optional: a list of functions as arguments.
  To create a Stimulus Controller within a module, pass it as either `--module NAME`
  or `--module=NAME`.
  The file lives in `frotend/controllers`, or in
  `frontend/controllers/{module}` if module is present.

Example:
  `rails generate stimulus_controller Modal open close`

  This will create:
    frontend/controllers/modal_controler.js

